msgctxt "mn139:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 139 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 139 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn139:0.2"
msgid "Araṇavibhaṅgasutta "
msgstr "The Analysis of Non-Conflict "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, pts-vp-pli3.230, sc1
msgctxt "mn139:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn139:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

msgctxt "mn139:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants, "

msgctxt "mn139:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn139:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "mn139:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2
msgctxt "mn139:2.1"
msgid "“araṇavibhaṅgaṃ vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I shall teach you the analysis of non-conflict. "

msgctxt "mn139:2.2"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn139:2.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "mn139:2.4"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3, sc2
msgctxt "mn139:3.1"
msgid "“Na kāmasukhamanuyuñjeyya hīnaṃ gammaṃ pothujjanikaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, na ca attakilamathānuyogamanuyuñjeyya dukkhaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ. "
msgstr "“Don’t indulge in sensual pleasures, which are low, crude, ordinary, ignoble, and pointless. And don’t indulge in self-mortification, which is painful, ignoble, and pointless. "

msgctxt "mn139:3.2"
msgid "Ete kho, bhikkhave, ubho ante anupagamma majjhimā paṭipadā tathāgatena abhisambuddhā, cakkhukaraṇī ñāṇakaraṇī upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattati. "
msgstr "Avoiding these two extremes, the Realized One woke up by understanding the middle way, which gives vision and knowledge, and leads to peace, direct knowledge, awakening, and extinguishment. "

msgctxt "mn139:3.3"
msgid "Ussādanañca jaññā, apasādanañca jaññā; "
msgstr "Know what it means to flatter and to rebuke. "

#. VAR: apasādeyya → nāpasādeyya (bj)
msgctxt "mn139:3.4"
msgid "ussādanañca ñatvā apasādanañca ñatvā nevussādeyya, na apasādeyya, dhammameva deseyya. "
msgstr "Knowing these, avoid them, and just teach Dhamma. "

msgctxt "mn139:3.5"
msgid "Sukhavinicchayaṃ jaññā; "
msgstr "Know how to assess different kinds of pleasure. "

msgctxt "mn139:3.6"
msgid "sukhavinicchayaṃ ñatvā ajjhattaṃ sukhamanuyuñjeyya. "
msgstr "Knowing this, pursue inner bliss. "

#. VAR: na khīṇaṃ → nātikhīṇaṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "mn139:3.7"
msgid "Rahovādaṃ na bhāseyya, sammukhā na khīṇaṃ bhaṇe. "
msgstr "Don’t talk behind people’s backs, and don’t speak sharply in their presence. "

msgctxt "mn139:3.8"
msgid "Ataramānova bhāseyya, no taramāno. "
msgstr "Don’t speak hurriedly. "

msgctxt "mn139:3.9"
msgid "Janapadaniruttiṃ nābhiniveseyya, samaññaṃ nātidhāveyyāti—"
msgstr "Don’t insist on local terminology and don’t override normal usage. "

msgctxt "mn139:3.10"
msgid "ayamuddeso araṇavibhaṅgassa. "
msgstr "This is the recitation passage for the analysis of non-conflict. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4, pts-vp-pli3.231, sc3
msgctxt "mn139:4.1"
msgid "‘Na kāmasukhamanuyuñjeyya hīnaṃ gammaṃ pothujjanikaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, na ca attakilamathānuyogamanuyuñjeyya dukkhaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitan’ti—"
msgstr "‘Don’t indulge in sensual pleasures, which are low, crude, ordinary, ignoble, and pointless. And don’t indulge in self-mortification, which is painful, ignoble, and pointless.’ "

msgctxt "mn139:4.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ; Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it? "

msgctxt "mn139:4.3"
msgid "Yo kāmapaṭisandhisukhino somanassānuyogo hīno gammo pothujjaniko anariyo anatthasaṃhito, sadukkho eso dhammo saupaghāto saupāyāso sapariḷāho; micchāpaṭipadā. "
msgstr "Pleasure linked to sensuality is low, crude, ordinary, ignoble, and pointless. Indulging in such happiness is a principle beset by pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the wrong way. "

msgctxt "mn139:4.4"
msgid "Yo kāmapaṭisandhisukhino somanassānuyogaṃ ananuyogo hīnaṃ gammaṃ pothujjanikaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, adukkho eso dhammo anupaghāto anupāyāso apariḷāho; sammāpaṭipadā. "
msgstr "Breaking off such indulgence is a principle free of pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the right way. "

msgctxt "mn139:4.5"
msgid "Yo attakilamathānuyogo dukkho anariyo anatthasaṃhito, sadukkho eso dhammo saupaghāto saupāyāso sapariḷāho; micchāpaṭipadā. "
msgstr "Indulging in self-mortification is painful, ignoble, and pointless. It is a principle beset by pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the wrong way. "

msgctxt "mn139:4.6"
msgid "Yo attakilamathānuyogaṃ ananuyogo dukkhaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, adukkho eso dhammo anupaghāto anupāyāso apariḷāho; sammāpaṭipadā. "
msgstr "Breaking off such indulgence is a principle free of pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the right way. "

msgctxt "mn139:4.7"
msgid "‘Na kāmasukhamanuyuñjeyya hīnaṃ gammaṃ pothujjanikaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, na ca attakilamathānuyogaṃ anuyuñjeyya dukkhaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitan’ti—"
msgstr "‘Don’t indulge in sensual pleasures, which are low, crude, ordinary, ignoble, and pointless. And don’t indulge in self-mortification, which is painful, ignoble, and pointless.’ "

msgctxt "mn139:4.8"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya5, sc4
msgctxt "mn139:5.1"
msgid "‘Ete kho ubho ante anupagamma majjhimā paṭipadā tathāgatena abhisambuddhā, cakkhukaraṇī ñāṇakaraṇī upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattatī’ti—"
msgstr "‘Avoiding these two extremes, the Realized One woke up by understanding the middle way, which gives vision and knowledge, and leads to peace, direct knowledge, awakening, and extinguishment.’ "

msgctxt "mn139:5.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it? "

msgctxt "mn139:5.3"
msgid "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "It is simply this noble eightfold path, that is: "

msgctxt "mn139:5.4"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi, sammāsaṅkappo, sammāvācā, sammākammanto, sammāājīvo, sammāvāyāmo, sammāsati, sammāsamādhi. "
msgstr "right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. "

msgctxt "mn139:5.5"
msgid "‘Ete kho ubho ante anupagamma majjhimā paṭipadā tathāgatena abhisambuddhā, cakkhukaraṇī ñāṇakaraṇī upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattatī’ti—"
msgstr "‘Avoiding these two extremes, the Realized One woke up by understanding the middle way, which gives vision and knowledge, and leads to peace, direct knowledge, awakening, and extinguishment.’ "

msgctxt "mn139:5.6"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya6, sc5
msgctxt "mn139:6.1"
msgid "‘Ussādanañca jaññā, apasādanañca jaññā; "
msgstr "‘Know what it means to flatter and to rebuke. "

msgctxt "mn139:6.2"
msgid "ussādanañca ñatvā apasādanañca ñatvā nevussādeyya, na apasādeyya, dhammameva deseyyā’ti—"
msgstr "Knowing these, avoid them, and just teach Dhamma.’ "

msgctxt "mn139:6.3"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya7
msgctxt "mn139:7.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, ussādanā ca hoti apasādanā ca, no ca dhammadesanā? "
msgstr "And how is there flattering and rebuking without teaching Dhamma? "

msgctxt "mn139:7.2"
msgid "‘Ye kāmapaṭisandhisukhino somanassānuyogaṃ anuyuttā hīnaṃ gammaṃ pothujjanikaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, sabbe te sadukkhā saupaghātā saupāyāsā sapariḷāhā micchāpaṭipannā’ti—"
msgstr "In speaking like this, some are rebuked: ‘Pleasure linked to sensuality is low, crude, ordinary, ignoble, and pointless. All those who indulge in such happiness are beset by pain, harm, stress, and fever, and they are practicing the wrong way.’ "

#. VAR: vadaṃ → iti paraṃ (mr)
msgctxt "mn139:7.3"
msgid "iti vadaṃ ittheke apasādeti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "mn139:7.4"
msgid "‘Ye kāmapaṭisandhisukhino somanassānuyogaṃ ananuyuttā hīnaṃ gammaṃ pothujjanikaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, sabbe te adukkhā anupaghātā anupāyāsā apariḷāhā sammāpaṭipannā’ti—"
msgstr "In speaking like this, some are flattered: ‘Pleasure linked to sensuality is low, crude, ordinary, ignoble, and pointless. All those who have broken off such indulgence are free of pain, harm, stress, and fever, and they are practicing the right way.’ "

msgctxt "mn139:7.5"
msgid "iti vadaṃ ittheke ussādeti. "
msgstr " "

