#. REF: nya9, pts-vp-pli3.234, sc17
msgctxt "mn139:9.1"
msgid "‘Sukhavinicchayaṃ jaññā; "
msgstr "‘Know how to assess different kinds of pleasure. "

msgctxt "mn139:9.2"
msgid "sukhavinicchayaṃ ñatvā ajjhattaṃ sukhamanuyuñjeyyā’ti—"
msgstr "Knowing this, pursue inner bliss.’ "

msgctxt "mn139:9.3"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it? "

msgctxt "mn139:9.4"
msgid "Pañcime, bhikkhave, kāmaguṇā. "
msgstr "There are these five kinds of sensual stimulation. "

msgctxt "mn139:9.5"
msgid "Katame pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "mn139:9.6"
msgid "Cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā, "
msgstr "Sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. "

msgctxt "mn139:9.7"
msgid "sotaviññeyyā saddā … "
msgstr "Sounds known by the ear … "

msgctxt "mn139:9.8"
msgid "ghānaviññeyyā gandhā … "
msgstr "Smells known by the nose … "

msgctxt "mn139:9.9"
msgid "jivhāviññeyyā rasā … "
msgstr "Tastes known by the tongue … "

msgctxt "mn139:9.10"
msgid "kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā—"
msgstr "Touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. "

msgctxt "mn139:9.11"
msgid "ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca kāmaguṇā. "
msgstr "These are the five kinds of sensual stimulation. "

msgctxt "mn139:9.12"
msgid "Yaṃ kho, bhikkhave, ime pañca kāmaguṇe paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ idaṃ vuccati kāmasukhaṃ mīḷhasukhaṃ puthujjanasukhaṃ anariyasukhaṃ. "
msgstr "The pleasure and happiness that arise from these five kinds of sensual stimulation is called sensual pleasure—a filthy, common, ignoble pleasure. "

msgctxt "mn139:9.13"
msgid "‘Na āsevitabbaṃ, na bhāvetabbaṃ, na bahulīkātabbaṃ, bhāyitabbaṃ etassa sukhassā’ti—vadāmi. "
msgstr "Such pleasure should not be cultivated or developed, but should be feared, I say. "

msgctxt "mn139:9.14"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Now, take a mendicant who, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected. "

msgctxt "mn139:9.15"
msgid "Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter and remain in the second absorption … "

msgctxt "mn139:9.16"
msgid "Pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "third absorption … "

msgctxt "mn139:9.17"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "fourth absorption. "

msgctxt "mn139:9.18"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati nekkhammasukhaṃ pavivekasukhaṃ upasamasukhaṃ sambodhisukhaṃ. "
msgstr "This is called the pleasure of renunciation, the pleasure of seclusion, the pleasure of peace, the pleasure of awakening. "

msgctxt "mn139:9.19"
msgid "‘Āsevitabbaṃ, bhāvetabbaṃ, bahulīkātabbaṃ, na bhāyitabbaṃ etassa sukhassā’ti—vadāmi. "
msgstr "Such pleasure should be cultivated and developed, and should not be feared, I say. "

msgctxt "mn139:9.20"
msgid "‘Sukhavinicchayaṃ jaññā; "
msgstr "‘Know how to assess different kinds of pleasure. "

msgctxt "mn139:9.21"
msgid "sukhavinicchayaṃ ñatvā ajjhattaṃ sukhamanuyuñjeyyā’ti—"
msgstr "Knowing this, pursue inner bliss.’ "

msgctxt "mn139:9.22"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya10, sc18
msgctxt "mn139:10.1"
msgid "‘Rahovādaṃ na bhāseyya, sammukhā na khīṇaṃ bhaṇe’ti—"
msgstr "‘Don’t talk behind people’s backs, and don’t speak sharply in their presence.’ "

msgctxt "mn139:10.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s what I said, "

msgctxt "mn139:10.3"
msgid "Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "but why did I say it? "

#. VAR: sasakkaṃ → sampattaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "mn139:10.4"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, yaṃ jaññā rahovādaṃ abhūtaṃ atacchaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ sasakkaṃ taṃ rahovādaṃ na bhāseyya. "
msgstr "When you know that what you say behind someone’s back is untrue, false, and harmful, then if at all possible you should not speak. "

msgctxt "mn139:10.5"
msgid "Yampi jaññā rahovādaṃ bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ tassapi sikkheyya avacanāya. "
msgstr "When you know that what you say behind someone’s back is true and correct, but harmful, then you should train yourself not to speak. "

msgctxt "mn139:10.6"
msgid "Yañca kho jaññā rahovādaṃ bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ atthasaṃhitaṃ tatra kālaññū assa tassa rahovādassa vacanāya. "
msgstr "When you know that what you say behind someone’s back is true, correct, and beneficial, then you should know the right time to speak. "

msgctxt "mn139:10.7"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, yaṃ jaññā sammukhā khīṇavādaṃ abhūtaṃ atacchaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ sasakkaṃ taṃ sammukhā khīṇavādaṃ na bhāseyya. "
msgstr "When you know that your sharp words in someone’s presence are untrue, false, and harmful, then if at all possible you should not speak. "

msgctxt "mn139:10.8"
msgid "Yampi jaññā sammukhā khīṇavādaṃ bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ tassapi sikkheyya avacanāya. "
msgstr "When you know that your sharp words in someone’s presence are true and correct, but harmful, then you should train yourself not to speak. "

msgctxt "mn139:10.9"
msgid "Yañca kho jaññā sammukhā khīṇavādaṃ bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ atthasaṃhitaṃ tatra kālaññū assa tassa sammukhā khīṇavādassa vacanāya. "
msgstr "When you know that your sharp words in someone’s presence are true, correct, and beneficial, then you should know the right time to speak. "

msgctxt "mn139:10.10"
msgid "‘Rahovādaṃ na bhāseyya, sammukhā na khīṇaṃ bhaṇe’ti—"
msgstr "‘Don’t talk behind people’s backs, and don’t speak sharply in their presence.’ "

msgctxt "mn139:10.11"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya11, sc19
msgctxt "mn139:11.1"
msgid "‘Ataramānova bhāseyya no taramāno’ti—"
msgstr "‘Don’t speak hurriedly.’ "

msgctxt "mn139:11.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it? "

#. VAR: upahaññati → ūhaññati (si)
msgctxt "mn139:11.3"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, taramānassa bhāsato kāyopi kilamati, cittampi upahaññati, saropi upahaññati, kaṇṭhopi āturīyati, avisaṭṭhampi hoti aviññeyyaṃ taramānassa bhāsitaṃ. "
msgstr "When speaking hurriedly, your body gets tired, your mind gets stressed, your voice gets stressed, your throat gets sore, and your words become unclear and hard to understand. "

msgctxt "mn139:11.4"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ataramānassa bhāsato kāyopi na kilamati, cittampi na upahaññati, saropi na upahaññati, kaṇṭhopi na āturīyati, visaṭṭhampi hoti viññeyyaṃ ataramānassa bhāsitaṃ. "
msgstr "When not speaking hurriedly, your body doesn’t get tired, your mind doesn’t get stressed, your voice doesn’t get stressed, your throat doesn’t get sore, and your words are clear and easy to understand. "

msgctxt "mn139:11.5"
msgid "‘Ataramānova bhāseyya, no taramāno’ti—"
msgstr "‘Don’t speak hurriedly.’ "

msgctxt "mn139:11.6"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya12, pts-vp-pli3.235, sc20
msgctxt "mn139:12.1"
msgid "‘Janapadaniruttiṃ nābhiniveseyya, samaññaṃ nātidhāveyyā’ti—"
msgstr "‘Don’t insist on local terminology and don’t override normal usage.’ "

msgctxt "mn139:12.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it? "

msgctxt "mn139:12.3"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, janapadaniruttiyā ca abhiniveso hoti samaññāya ca atisāro? "
msgstr "And how do you insist on local terminology and override normal usage? "

#. VAR: dhāropan’ti → harosanti (s1-3, km)
#. VAR: vittan’ti → vitthanti (bj, pts1) | piṭṭhanti (s1-3, km)
#. VAR: pisīlavan’ti → pipilanti (s1-3, km) | pisīlanti (pts1)
msgctxt "mn139:12.4"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, tadevekaccesu janapadesu ‘pātī’ti sañjānanti, ‘pattan’ti sañjānanti, ‘vittan’ti sañjānanti, ‘sarāvan’ti sañjānanti ‘dhāropan’ti sañjānanti, ‘poṇan’ti sañjānanti, ‘pisīlavan’ti sañjānanti. "
msgstr "It’s when in different localities the same thing is known as a ‘plate’, a ‘bowl’, a ‘cup’, a ‘dish’, a ‘basin’, a ‘tureen’, or a ‘porringer’. "

#. VAR: parāmāsā → parāmassa (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn139:12.5"
msgid "Iti yathā yathā naṃ tesu tesu janapadesu sañjānanti tathā tathā thāmasā parāmāsā abhinivissa voharati: "
msgstr "And however it is known in those various localities, you speak accordingly, obstinately sticking to that and insisting: "

msgctxt "mn139:12.6"
msgid "‘idameva saccaṃ, moghamaññan’ti. "
msgstr "‘This is the only truth, other ideas are silly.’ "

msgctxt "mn139:12.7"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, janapadaniruttiyā ca abhiniveso hoti samaññāya ca atisāro. "
msgstr "That’s how you insist on local terminology and override normal usage. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21
msgctxt "mn139:12.8"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, janapadaniruttiyā ca anabhiniveso hoti samaññāya ca anatisāro? "
msgstr "And how do you not insist on local terminology and not override normal usage? "

msgctxt "mn139:12.9"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, tadevekaccesu janapadesu ‘pātī’ti sañjānanti, ‘pattan’ti sañjānanti, ‘vittan’ti sañjānanti, ‘sarāvan’ti sañjānanti, ‘dhāropan’ti sañjānanti, ‘poṇan’ti sañjānanti, ‘pisīlavan’ti sañjānanti. "
msgstr "It’s when in different localities the same thing is known as a ‘plate’, a ‘bowl’, a ‘cup’, a ‘dish’, a ‘basin’, a ‘tureen’, or a ‘porringer’. "

#. VAR: idaṃ kira me → idaṃ kira te ca (mr)
msgctxt "mn139:12.10"
msgid "Iti yathā yathā naṃ tesu tesu janapadesu sañjānanti ‘idaṃ kira me āyasmanto sandhāya voharantī’ti tathā tathā voharati aparāmasaṃ. "
msgstr "And however it is known in those various localities, you speak accordingly, thinking: ‘It seems that the venerables are referring to this.’ "

msgctxt "mn139:12.11"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, janapadaniruttiyā ca anabhiniveso hoti, samaññāya ca anatisāro. "
msgstr "That’s how you don’t insist on local terminology and don’t override normal usage. "

msgctxt "mn139:12.12"
msgid "‘Janapadaniruttiṃ nābhiniveseyya samaññaṃ nātidhāveyyā’ti—"
msgstr "‘Don’t insist on local terminology and don’t override normal usage.’ "

msgctxt "mn139:12.13"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya13, sc22
msgctxt "mn139:13.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, yo kāmapaṭisandhisukhino somanassānuyogo hīno gammo pothujjaniko anariyo anatthasaṃhito, sadukkho eso dhammo saupaghāto saupāyāso sapariḷāho; "
msgstr "Now, mendicants, pleasure linked to sensuality is low, crude, ordinary, ignoble, and pointless. Indulging in such happiness is a principle beset by pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the wrong way. "

msgctxt "mn139:13.2"
msgid "micchāpaṭipadā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn139:13.3"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo saraṇo. "
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle beset by conflict. "

msgctxt "mn139:13.4"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, yo kāmapaṭisandhisukhino somanassānuyogaṃ ananuyogo hīnaṃ gammaṃ pothujjanikaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, adukkho eso dhammo anupaghāto anupāyāso apariḷāho; "
msgstr "Breaking off such indulgence is a principle free of pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the right way. "

msgctxt "mn139:13.5"
msgid "sammāpaṭipadā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn139:13.6"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo araṇo. "
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle free of conflict. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc23
msgctxt "mn139:13.7"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, yo attakilamathānuyogo dukkho anariyo anatthasaṃhito, sadukkho eso dhammo saupaghāto saupāyāso sapariḷāho; "
msgstr "Indulging in self-mortification is painful, ignoble, and pointless. It is a principle beset by pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the wrong way. "

msgctxt "mn139:13.8"
msgid "micchāpaṭipadā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn139:13.9"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo saraṇo. "
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle beset by conflict. "

msgctxt "mn139:13.10"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, yo attakilamathānuyogaṃ ananuyogo dukkhaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, adukkho eso dhammo anupaghāto anupāyāso apariḷāho; "
msgstr "Breaking off such indulgence is a principle free of pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the right way. "

msgctxt "mn139:13.11"
msgid "sammāpaṭipadā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn139:13.12"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo araṇo. "
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle free of conflict. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.236, sc24
msgctxt "mn139:13.13"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, yāyaṃ majjhimā paṭipadā tathāgatena abhisambuddhā, cakkhukaraṇī ñāṇakaraṇī upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattati, adukkho eso dhammo anupaghāto anupāyāso apariḷāho; "
msgstr "The middle way by which the Realized One was awakened gives vision and knowledge, and leads to peace, direct knowledge, awakening, and extinguishment. It is a principle free of pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the right way. "

msgctxt "mn139:13.14"
msgid "sammāpaṭipadā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn139:13.15"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo araṇo. "
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle free of conflict. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc25
msgctxt "mn139:13.16"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, yāyaṃ ussādanā ca apasādanā ca no ca dhammadesanā, sadukkho eso dhammo saupaghāto saupāyāso sapariḷāho; "
msgstr "Flattering and rebuking without teaching Dhamma is a principle beset by pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the wrong way. "

msgctxt "mn139:13.17"
msgid "micchāpaṭipadā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn139:13.18"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo saraṇo. "
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle beset by conflict. "

msgctxt "mn139:13.19"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, yāyaṃ nevussādanā ca na apasādanā ca dhammadesanā ca, adukkho eso dhammo anupaghāto anupāyāso apariḷāho; "
msgstr "Neither flattering nor rebuking, and just teaching Dhamma is a principle free of pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the right way. "

msgctxt "mn139:13.20"
msgid "sammāpaṭipadā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn139:13.21"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo araṇo. "
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle free of conflict. "

